v:4 c:$ m:portfolio role:dev x:vue-router-dynamic
gate: LOCKED

task: Wire the registry (T10) into vue-router as dynamic, lazy-loaded routes. Each room gets `/rooms/<slug>` URL with code-splitting. Includes 404 handler for unknown slugs and pitch-aware analytics tagging.

requires: [vue, vite, typescript]
out:
  - app/src/router/rooms.ts
  - app/src/router/index.ts (extend from T06)
  - app/src/views/RoomNotFound.vue
  - app/src/composables/useRoomAnalytics.ts

route-shape:
  base: /rooms/:slug
  meta:
    - layout: 'room'         (full-screen, no bottom-nav padding)
    - kind: 'room'           (vs 'system' for app shell pages)
    - room: RoomManifest     (resolved at navigation guard, attached to route)
  component: () => loadRoomComponent(slug)  (from registry T10)
  beforeEnter:
    - resolve manifest via getRoomBySlug
    - if null → redirect to /rooms/__not-found__
    - if status==='archived' → render Room with archived banner
    - log to room_dwell on leave (pitch rooms tagged `pitch:<slug>`)

dynamic-import-strategy:
  - Vite chunk naming: `room-<slug>.[hash].js`
  - prefetch hint on Wall hover (link rel=prefetch)
  - error boundary: if chunk fails, show RoomNotFound with retry

constraints:
  - Routes registered ONCE at app boot, derived from getAllRooms() (T10).
  - Hot-reload: adding a new room dir + restart dev = route appears.
  - Pitch rooms: route exists but NOT linked from Wall (T13 enforces).
  - Sitemap helper: `getSitemapPaths()` returns ONLY visibility==='public' slugs.

constraints-on-room-component:
  - Default-export the Vue component (not named).
  - Component receives no props — accesses manifest via `useRoute().meta.room`.
  - Free to override layout via `defineOptions({ inheritAttrs: false })`.

done:
  - Adding a room via T11 CLI → boot dev → URL /rooms/<slug> renders without manual edits.
  - Unknown slug shows RoomNotFound with link back to /work.
  - Each room loads as separate chunk (verified in Network tab).
  - Pitch room visit logs `pitch:<slug>` event in room_dwell (Supabase Studio check).
  - Reduced-motion preference still honored across all room transitions.
